Written evidence from Janssen (LTC 74)[bold]Introduction[bold]1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Janssen is the Pharmaceutical Operating Company of the Johnson &amp; Jo
[normal]hnson family of companies. 
[normal]Johnson &amp; Johnson is the largest healthcare company in the world and has a tradition of commitment to the UK, being established in the UK since 1927. Today, Johnson &amp; Johnson employs circa 5,000 people across the UK. We have manufacturing sites in Inverness, Blackpool, Livingston, Cardiff and research and development facilities in Inverness, Leeds, and High Wycombe.
[normal]2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]We are committed to delivering innovative medicines which make an important difference to the lives of patients with serious health conditions such as hepatitis C, HIV, schizophrenia and cancer.
[normal] 
[normal]Janssen is committed to providing medicines that have a real impact on the lives of patients and reduce health inequalities. We welcome the opportunity to respond to this inquiry.
[normal]3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]We are pleased that diabetes and severe mental health conditions are recognised as areas that need to be reviewed as part of this inquiry. 
[normal]4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Janssen also believes that there are further conditions that should be considered within this enquiry, including psoriasis
[normal] and 
[normal]HIV
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]5
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]As recognised by the inquiry, all long-term conditions 
[normal](LTCs) 
[normal]present a huge burden to the NHS and social care system accounting f
[normal]or 70% of health and care spend, affecting over 20 million people in England,
[normal] however equal recognition 
[normal]should be given 
[normal]to the impact 
[normal]of 
[normal]caring for someone with a LTC. Provisions for carers should be examined by the Health Committee as they play an integral role in delivering care and treatment to those affected. 
[normal]6
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Integral to the management of all LTCs is the need for excellent patient information and support. In the advent of the 
[normal]recent 
[normal]NHS reforms
[normal],
[normal] it is crucial that attention is given to the provision of accurate, reputable advice on how to manage a LTC. This information can be used to empower a patient (or their carer) to take responsibility for their own condition and optimise their personal management.
[normal] 
[normal]7
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]It is critical that patients have access to cost-effective innovation as part of an integrated pathway of care and that CCGs are measured, incentivised and rewarded for delivering excellence in the care of patients with LTCs. Uptake of new technologies that improve outcomes must be central to this in the new NHS.
[normal]Diabetes[bold]8
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The scale of the challenge that diabetes presents in the UK should not be underestimated, with high, recorded prevalence of diabetes and associated co-morbidities across the country, as well as high estimations of undiagnosed populations. Early diagnosis, preventative treatment and multi-disciplinary team support of the patients will undoubtedly mean increased financ
[normal]ial pressure in the short-term; h
[normal]owever, leaving these patients undiagnosed until further
[normal] complications ensue
[normal] will result in a heavier
[normal] total
[normal] cost burden to 
[normal]the 
[normal]NHS
[normal].
[normal]9
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]It is fundamentally important to have clear
[normal] consistent
[normal] processes 
[normal]across all CCGs 
[normal]in place for early diagn
[normal]osis and management of diabetes, with plans which are
[normal] specific
[normal] and measurable
[normal]. Short-term investment in early detection, diagnosis and good management will lead not only 
[normal]to good practice, but also long-
[normal]term savings result
[normal]ing
[normal] from 
[normal]avoiding complications
[normal] and late identification of the disease.
